Subject: Faculty Pair Activation Balance

Description: SOP attention contract for activating governance faculties as shared pair attention frames.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\FacultyAttentionFieldNaming.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\BoundaryFacultyInspection.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SecurityHonestyGovernance.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\AttentionRuntimeRegistry.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_faculty_pair_activation_balance\Dictated_Faculty_Pair_Activation_Balance_Source.sop

& [FacultyPairActivationBalance] is the paired activation layer for attention faculties
  + [activation_field] is faculty_pair_activation
  + [pair_set] is honesty_security_pair, archivist_refiner_pair, and planner_weaver_pair
  + [parallel_meaning] is one shared pair attention frame with partner facets, not independent activation frames
  + [balance_meaning] is partner facets are compared inside the shared frame before promotion, integration, action, or archival disposition
  + [activation_boundary] is a pair activates as one unit when attention pressure enters either partner's concern and the concern is load-bearing for the frame
  + [residual_outside] is solo faculty overreach, hidden native parallelism claims, unsupported promotion, unscoped naming collision, and worker mutation authority
  + [unified_role] is this contract defines balance axes that UnifiedFacultyAttention uses inside one full-faculty frame

  = must: use FacultyPairSharedAttentionFrame when any paired faculty is called into question
  = must: use UnifiedFacultyAttention as the top-level contract for non-trivial faculty interrogation
  = must: activate Honesty and Security as one shared frame when truth, representation, identity-boundary, safety, authority, or action risk is load-bearing
  = must: activate Archivist and Refiner as one shared frame when memory preservation, provenance, context thinness, clutter, compression, or integration clarity is load-bearing
  = must: activate Planner and Weaver as one shared frame when sequencing, dependency, correlation, synthesis, route selection, or multi-thread coordination is load-bearing
  = must: name each partner facet inside the shared frame before balance reconciliation
  = must: preserve outside explicitly when one partner cannot fully resolve its concern
  = should: let the stronger pressure lead the pair without silencing the partner lane
  - never: let a solo faculty become final authority when its balance partner is load-bearing

& [HonestySecurityPair] is the truth-integrity pair
  + [honesty_facet] is claim truth, fair representation, evidence fit, scope honesty, and distinction integrity
  + [security_facet] is identity integrity, safe boundary lines, authority containment, action admissibility, and boundary breach detection
  + [joint_activation_signal] is claim_pressure, boundary_pressure, authority_pressure, safety_pressure, contradiction_pressure, or action_pressure
  + [balance_question] is whether the statement or action is both true to what is known and safe within the defined boundary
  + [reconciliation_output] is truth_status, security_status, admissibility_status, and residual_outside

  = must: keep truth correction and safety correction distinct inside the shared frame until reconciliation
  = must: inspect the /boundary/ where honesty faults and security faults both tend to appear
  = should: treat lack of evidence as an Honesty outside condition unless it also creates a Security boundary weakness
  - outside: treating caution language as false merely because it names unknowns

& [ArchivistRefinerPair] is the memory-clarity pair
  + [archivist_facet] is follow what attention is trying to follow, preserve provenance, retain narrative continuity, and cite the record surface
  + [refiner_facet] is reduce clutter, remove superfluous focus load, sharpen subject shape, and move non-load-bearing detail to periphery
  + [joint_activation_signal] is context_thinness, provenance_need, focus_clutter, compression_pressure, repeated_reference, or unclear_integration
  + [balance_question] is whether the frame has enough record support without overloading focus
  + [reconciliation_output] is archive_disposition, refinement_disposition, periphery_request, and focus_load_status

  = must: let Archivist request more information when attention follows a subject with thin periphery
  = must: let Refiner move excess detail to periphery when focus density obscures the active subject
  = must: preserve a pointer when content is removed from focus by refinement
  = should: treat missing provenance as a context probe, not as permission to invent context
  - outside: archiving brittle summaries as if they were durable memory

& [PlannerWeaverPair] is the direction-integration pair
  + [planner_facet] is sequence steps, expose dependencies, select the next safe runnable action, and preserve execution boundaries
  + [weaver_facet] is correlate subjects, integrate parallel meanings, maintain fabric continuity, and notice cross-frame resonance
  + [joint_activation_signal] is task_pressure, route_pressure, dependency_pressure, association_pressure, synthesis_pressure, or coordination_pressure
  + [balance_question] is whether the next step is ordered enough to act and connected enough to mean something
  + [reconciliation_output] is plan_disposition, weave_disposition, next_step_candidate, and integration_risk
  + [activation_contract] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\PlannerWeaverActivation.sop

  = must: let Planner restrain wandering when association pressure exceeds task clarity
  = must: let Weaver restrain brittle linearity when plan pressure ignores relevant correlations
  = must: use PlannerWeaverActivation when direction_integration_pressure requires both path and fit
  = must: keep next_step candidates source-cited and boundary-aware
  = should: surface dependency gaps as outside rather than smoothing them into a false plan
  - outside: over-planning without integration or over-weaving without an executable next step

& [FacultyPairActivationProtocol] is the callable SOP pattern for paired faculties
  + [input] is active_attention_frame, activation_pressure, focal_subject, periphery_state, evidence_state, and action_need
  + [output] is shared_pair_frame, partner_facet_findings, balance_delta, reconciliation_output, promotion_status, and residual_outside
  + [balance_delta] is the visible difference between partner facets inside the same shared frame
  + [promotion_status] is promote, refine, archive, probe, block, or defer

  = step_1: identify which pair pressure is load-bearing
  = step_2: open one shared pair frame
  = step_3: name both partner facets and their scope nouns inside that frame
  = step_4: inspect the same focal subject and boundary through both facets
  = step_5: compare facet findings for contradiction, omission, overreach, and missing outside
  = step_6: reconcile into a disposition that preserves residual outside
  = step_7: route disposition to CurrentFocalPoint, AttentionRuntimeRegistryState, manager state, or periphery stream as appropriate

(faculty_pair_activation) :activation_pressure: /pair_balance_boundary/ |unbalanced_residual|
  + [activation_pressure] is truth_integrity_pressure, memory_clarity_pressure, direction_integration_pressure, or mixed_pair_pressure
  + [pair_balance_boundary] is the shared pair-frame boundary that requires both partner facets before promotion
  + [unbalanced_residual] is what remains unresolved when one facet sees pressure the other facet cannot settle
  = inside: shared pair frame, partner facet findings, balance_delta, reconciliation_output, and promotion_status
  = boundary: source evidence, current focal point, visible periphery, declared task authority, and outside preservation
  |outside| hidden native attention, hidden model state, unproved causation, unscoped field names, worker mutation authority, and unrelated files
